mode script

// Regression for issue #312: a top-level numeric `for i in 0..N` loop in a
// `mode script` unit crashed the typer with an OutOfBounds panic instead of
// type-checking (identically interpreted and compiled).
//
// infer_body_unit walked the top-level statements with a `while i < len` loop
// and, after each infer_body_stmt, read body.children[i] for
// constfolder_classify_stmt. infer_body_stmt takes `mut i` by reference and
// rewinds it (i--) to reprocess a statement it desugared: a single top-level
// ForIn desugars to a Body block and the i-- underflowed the USize index, so
// the trailing body.children[i] read went OutOfBounds. Function bodies went
// through infer_body, which has no trailing children[i] read, so only
// top-level `mode script` units crashed. The classify pass now runs over the
// finished body once, after the walk.

for i in 0..3 {
    println(i.to_str())
}
println("after")
for j in 3..0 {
    println(j.to_str())
}
